SIMPLE: toddy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Toddy
<hw>Tod"dy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Formed from Hind.
<ets>t⟦amac⟧<?/⟦imac⟧</ets> the juice of the palmyra tree, popularly,
<ets>toddy</ets>, fr. <ets>t⟦amac⟧<?/</ets> the palmyra tree, Skr.
<ets>t⟦amac⟧la</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A juice drawn from various
kinds of palms in the East Indies; or, a spirituous liquor procured from
it by fermentation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A mixture of spirit and hot water
sweetened.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Toddy</xex> differs from <xex>grog</xex> in having
a less proportion of spirit, and is being made hot and
sweetened.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Toddy bird</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a weaver
bird of the East Indies and India: -- so called from its fondness for
the juice of the palm.</cd> -- <col><b>Toddy cat</b></col>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the common paradoxure; the palm
cat.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

